276  ED       LOOPS              no           yes        Programming Constr=
uct 3: Iteration / Looping

Definition
    A loop repeats work.

DotTalk++ loop families
    LOOP ... ENDLOOP
    WHILE ... ENDWHILE
    UNTIL ... ENDUNTIL
    SCAN ... ENDSCAN

1. LOOP
    Repeats a fixed number of times.

    Example
        LOOP 3 TIMES
            ECHO HELLO
        ENDLOOP

2. WHILE
    Repeats while a condition stays true.

    Example concept
        WHILE counter &lt; 10
            ...
        ENDWHILE

3. UNTIL
    Repeats until a condition becomes true.

4. SCAN
    Record-oriented loop over table rows.

    Example
